      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Click the prominent ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "\"+\"",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " button in the top-left corner or the \"Add App\" option. A search bar appears. Type in the name of the website you want to turn into an app—let's use \"Notion\" as our example. WebCatalog's catalog will show pre-configured profiles for popular sites, which optimize settings like notifications and appearance. Select \"Notion\" from the list.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Step 3: Configure and Name Your App",
